# Time, windows & watermarking

## Two clocks

- **Processing time** — when Spark sees the row
- **Event time** — when it actually happened — the honest clock (watermark operates on it)

## Three window types (over event time)

- **Tumbling** — `window(ts, "5 min")` — fixed, non-overlapping
- **Sliding** — `window(ts, "5 min", "1 min")` — overlapping; event in multiple windows
- **Session** — `session_window(ts, "10 min")` — opens on activity, closes after a gap

## Watermarking

- `watermark = max(event_time) − delay`
- Before it → **dropped** · window ends at/before it → **closed** (state freed)
- `.withWatermark(col, "10 min")` **before** `groupBy` · **required** for `append` windowed aggs
